  "issue_number": 122,
  "issue_title": "feature: add task completion summary card",
  "issue_body": "## Problem\n\nAt the end of a local task, users need a concise summary of whether TouchPilot completed the task, stopped safely, failed, or needs more input. Without a final summary, the step timeline can be hard to interpret.\n\n## Proposed behavior\n\nAdd a completion summary card at the end of each local agent run. It should show final status, stop reason, step count, last verified state, and a short next action if applicable.\n\n## User workflow\n\nAfter a task finishes, the user sees \u201cCompleted\u201d, \u201cStopped\u201d, \u201cBlocked\u201d, or \u201cNeeds clarification\u201d with enough context to understand what happened.\n\n## Local-first impact\n\nThis makes local execution outcomes transparent without requiring users to inspect debug logs.\n\n## Safety and security considerations\n\nFailure and blocked summaries should avoid exposing raw tool args or screen text. Policy-blocked runs should explain the safety reason clearly.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- Summary card renders after every run stop.\n- Shows final status, stop reason, step count, and last verification outcome.\n- Distinguishes completed, failed, blocked, cancelled, and clarification-needed states.\n- Uses redacted display fields only.\n- Looks correct on narrow mobile screens.",
  "merged_at": "2026-06-02T12:17:03.000Z",
